aws_desc: Amazon Web Services (AWS) is a comprehensive, evolving cloud computing platform provided by Amazon. It offers a mix of infrastructure as a service (IaaS), platform as a service (PaaS), and packaged software as a service (SaaS) offerings. AWS services can offer organizations tools such as compute power, database storage, and content delivery services.
chakra_ui_desc: Chakra UI is a modern, accessible, and simple-to-use React UI library that provides a set of reusable and composable React components. It aims to make it easier for developers to build beautiful, responsive, and accessible user interfaces for their web applications. Chakra UI is designed with accessibility in mind, ensuring that applications built with it are accessible to as wide an audience as possible, including people with disabilities.

django_desc: Django is a high-level Python web framework that encourages rapid development and clean, pragmatic design. Built by experienced developers, it takes care of much of the hassle of web development, so you can focus on writing your app without needing to reinvent the wheel. It's free and open source.

expo_desc: Expo is an open-source platform for making universal native apps for Android, iOS, and the web with JavaScript and React. It simplifies the process of building and deploying mobile apps by providing a set of tools and services that abstract away much of the complexity involved in managing native development environments. With Expo, developers can develop and test their apps on real devices and emulators without having to configure native code, making the development process faster and accessible to those who might not have extensive experience with iOS or Android development.
firebase_desc: Firebase is a comprehensive app development platform provided by Google, offering a wide array of tools and services to help developers build, improve, and grow their apps. Its services are divided into three main categories: Build, Release & Monitor, and Engage, covering the entire app development lifecycle from development to deployment and analytics.
framer_motion_desc: Framer Motion is a popular open-source React library for creating animations and interactive animations in React applications. It's designed to be simple yet powerful, offering a comprehensive suite of animation features that can help enhance the user experience of web applications. Framer Motion provides a high level of control over animations while abstracting away much of the complexity involved in creating intricate animations.

nextjs_desc: Next.js is an open-source React front-end development web framework created by Vercel (formerly known as Zeit) that enables functionality such as server-side rendering and generating static websites for React-based web applications. It's designed to make it easy for developers to build fast, scalable, and user-friendly web applications with React.

postgresql_desc: PostgreSQL, often simply Postgres, is an advanced, open-source object-relational database system known for its reliability, robustness, and performance, especially when managing complex data workloads. PostgreSQL has been developed and improved over more than 30 years of engineering, boasting a strong reputation for its architecture, data integrity, and extensive feature set.
react_desc: React is a JavaScript library for building fast and interactive user interfaces for web applications. It is component-based, allowing developers to create large web applications that can change data, without reloading the page. React Native extends React's approach to mobile app development. Unlike tools that generate mobile app versions of a web app through webviews, React Native produces truly native apps for both Android and iOS platforms. It uses the same design as React, letting you compose a rich mobile UI from declarative components. With React Native, you write your UI using JavaScript and React, but the framework translates your components into platform-native components, allowing your app to access and use native platform capabilities.

supabase_desc: Supabase is an open-source Firebase alternative, offering developers a suite of tools to rapidly build and scale their applications. It provides a combination of key backend services that are typically required for web and mobile applications, aiming to increase development speed without locking in the developer to a specific framework or technology.
